author: Ryan Lovelace
title: Bush: Trump's attack on my brother is 'pathetic'
text:
Former Florida Gov. Jeb Bush is fighting back against Donald Trump's criticism of his brother George W. Bush's handling of the Sept. 11, 2001 terrorist attacks.
Trump took aim at the former president first in an interview published on Friday noting, "the World Trade Center came down during his time [in office]."
"He was president, OK?" Trump told Bloomberg . "Blame him, or don't blame him, but he was president. The World Trade Center came down during his reign."
Related Story: http://www.washingtonexaminer.com/article/2574118/ Bush responded on Twitter Friday afternoon and called the criticism "pathetic."
  U.S. jet in Afghanistan hit by small-arms fire The F-16 was able to land safely after the incident on Oct. 13, said Capt. Jeff Davis, a Pentagon spokesman.
By Jacqueline Klimas • 10/19/15 1:29 PM How pathetic for @realdonaldtrump to criticize the president for 9/11. We were attacked & my brother kept us safe.— Jeb Bush (@JebBush) October 16, 2015 
Bush and Trump are jockeying for supremacy in the Republican Party as the next presidential debate approaches. Trump remained number one in the Washington Examiner 's most recent power rankings and continues his lead in several national surveys regarding the GOP presidential field.
